===Alternative forms===
{{wikipedia}}
* [[aard-vark]], [[erdvark]]<ref>Gove, Philip Babcock (1976)</ref>

===Etymology===
From South African {{etyl|nl}} {{term|aardvarken}} ( > Afrikaans {{term|erdvark}}), from {{etyl|nl}} {{term|aarde||earth|lang=nl}} + {{etyl|nl}} {{term|varken||pig|lang=nl}}. Early European colonists in South Africa noticed that the animal was similar to a pig, while "aarde" hints at the animal's habit of burrowing.

===Pronunciation===
{{wikisource1911Enc|Aard-vark}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈɑː(ɹ)dˌvɑː(ɹ)k/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/":A(r\)d%vA:(r\)k/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑɹd.ˌvɑɹk/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"Ar\d%vAr\k/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[mammal]] ''[[Orycteropus afer]]'', of the order ''[[Tubulidentata]]'', somewhat resembling a [[pig]], common in some parts of sub-Saharan Africa. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#: ''The aardvark burrows in the ground and feeds mostly on termites, which it catches with its long, slimy tongue.
# {{slang|particularly in the southeast|_|US}} A [[silly]] or [[credulous]] person who is prone to [[mistakes]] or [[blunders]].
#: ''I walked into the wrong bathroom like a total '''aardvark'''.''

